Dinner time today with some Japanese friends:
During the dinner time, someone was doing something dangerous, so my friend told me that &ldquo;Abunai&rdquo; is dangerous in Japanese. Later on, one of my friends brought very yummy food, I said &ldquo;ちょっと危ない (Chotto Abunai means a little dangerous)&quot;, dangerous in the way that I tend to eat too much&hellip;
Then I thought of &ldquo;piri karai (means a little spicy)&rdquo;, I changed the saying to &ldquo;piri abunai!
